'''Kose no Kuromaro''' (巨勢 黒麻呂) is an aristocrat of the [[:en:Asuka period|Asuka Period]]. His name is also recorded as '''Kuromaru'''. His [[:en:Kabane|Surname]] is of the type [[:en:Omi (title)|Subject]]. He was the son of the [[:en:Minister of the Left|Minister of the Left]] {{ill|Kose Tokuda|ja|巨勢徳多|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Tokuda|qq=}}, and the father of {{ill|Kose Oharu|ja|巨勢邑治|lt=Oharu|lt_ja=邑治|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Oharu|qq=}} and {{ill|Kose Kooharu|ja|巨勢小邑治|lt=Kooharu|lt_ja=小邑治|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Kooharu|qq=}}.<ref>'Kōkei Honin': Clause of Kose no Asomi Sakaimaro in Tenpyō 9</ref> His court Rank, as indicated by the {{ill|26‐step Court Rank|ja|冠位二十六階|lt=Court Rank|lt_ja=冠位|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/26‐step Court Rank|qq=}}, was that of {{ill|Koshikinchu|ja|小錦中|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koshikinchu|qq=}} and [[:en:Chūnagon|Chunagon]], though there are doubts regarding his official positions.
== Analysis == Although many details of his career and life remain unclear, from the obituary of {{ill|Kose Oharu|ja|巨勢邑治|lt=Oharu|lt_ja=邑治|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Oharu|qq=}} in the [[:en:Shoku Nihongi|Shoku Nihongi]]<ref>'Shoku Nihongi': Kamiki 1, June 6 entry</ref> the following can be ascertained: # His court Rank, {{ill|Koshikinchu|ja|小錦中|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koshikinchu|qq=}}, was the 11th Rank of the 26‐step system established in February of the 3rd year of [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Emperor Tenji]]’s reign ({{ill|664|ja|664|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/664|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 600}}), and although it was a high Rank, by January of the 14th year of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}’s reign ({{ill|685|ja|685|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/685|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 600}}) the {{ill|48‐step Court Rank|ja|冠位・位階制度の変遷#冠位四十八階|lt=48‐step Court Rank|lt_ja=冠位四十八階|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/48‐step Court Rank|qq=}} was established. # [[:en:Chūnagon|Chunagon]] was established in April of the 2nd year of [[:en:Keiun|Keiun]] ({{ill|705|ja|705|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/705|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}) under the title of {{ill|Reigai-kan|ja|令外官|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Reigai-kan|qq=}}, a position that did not exist during the Tenji and Tenmu periods. It is presumed that once established during the Tenmu period the character “中” was later inserted into the title “納言”.<ref>{{ill|Kazuo Aoki|ja|青木和夫|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazuo Aoki|qq=}}: "Reading {{ill|Taku Tanaka|ja|田中卓|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taku Tanaka|qq=}}’s ‘Chunagon (Part 1)’" in ''Shoku Nihongi Kenkyū Ichi – Hachi''</ref> The title “Nagon” appears in instances such as in the 9th year of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ({{ill|680|ja|680|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/680|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 600}}) with {{ill|Toneri-ō|ja|舎人王|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toneri-ō|qq=}},<ref>'Nihon Shoki': Emperor Tenmu, 9th year, July 25 entry</ref> and in January of the 1st year of [[:en:Empress Jitō|Empress Jitō]] ({{ill|687|ja|687|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/687|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 600}}) with {{ill|Abe Goshujin|ja|阿倍御主人|lt=Fuse Goshujin|lt_ja=布勢御主人|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Abe Goshujin|qq=}}.<ref>'Nihon Shoki': Empress Jitō, January 1 entry</ref> Since no ministers were appointed during the Tenmu period, the position of Nagon was the highest administrative office. The title “Nagon” is of Chinese origin, as seen in the "Shuntian" of the [[:en:Book of Documents|Shu Jing]], and in the early Sui and Tang dynasties it was the title for the head ([[:en:Palace Attendant|Chamberlain]]) of the [[:en:Menxia Sheng|Monkashō]].
== Genealogy == * Father: {{ill|Kose Tokuda|ja|巨勢徳多|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Tokuda|qq=}} * Mother: Unknown * Children by an unknown consort: ** Son: {{ill|Kose Oharu|ja|巨勢邑治|lt=Oharu|lt_ja=邑治|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Oharu|qq=}} ** Son: {{ill|Kose Kooharu|ja|巨勢小邑治|lt=Kooharu|lt_ja=小邑治|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Kooharu|qq=}}
